==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Xanthochroism
<hw>Xan*thoch"ro*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Abnormal
coloration of feathers in which yellow replaces the normal color, as in
certain parrots. It is commonly due to lack of the dark pigment which
with yellow forms green.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xanthodontous</ent>⟦br⟧
